This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it proposes a new approach to training neural networks. The paper also involves experiments on popular datasets, which is a common characteristic of papers in the cs.LG sub-category. 

The paper also involves computer vision tasks such as image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. 

The use of binary weights and quantization in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category, which deals with the study of neural networks and their applications. 

The paper's focus on improving the efficiency of neural network training suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category, which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems. 

Finally, the paper's use of stochastic gradient descent and back-propagation suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category, which deals with the study of algorithms and data structures for efficient computation.
